name: Result-setter
Result message setter
func:
var tab = []
var gs = {}

var n = msg.payload.length

 //From the GS
gs.ergolmass = parseFloat(msg.payload[n-12])
gs.date = Date.parse(msg.payload[n-11])
gs.alti = parseFloat(msg.payload[n-10])
gs.sma = parseFloat(msg.payload[n-9])
gs.ecc = msg.payload[n-8]
gs.inc = parseFloat(msg.payload[n-7]).toFixed(4)
gs.raan = (parseFloat(msg.payload[n-6])).toFixed(4)
gs.aop = parseFloat(msg.payload[n-5]).toFixed(4)
gs.meananom = (parseFloat(msg.payload[n-4])+0.0).toFixed(4)
gs.meanmove = parseFloat(msg.payload[n-3]).toFixed(14)
gs.period = parseFloat(msg.payload[n-2])

// 090523 adding a null NAN undefiened detector it triggers also if all elements are null
msg.errorFlag=Object.values(gs).some((element) => isNaN(element)||element===null) || Object.values(gs).every((element) => element===0);
//
 
tab.push(gs)

msg.payload = tab
return msg;

name: Result message setter
func:
var tab = []
var gs = {}

var n = msg.payload.length

 //From the GS
gs.ergolmass = parseFloat(msg.payload[n-12])
gs.date = Date.parse(msg.payload[n-11])
gs.alti = parseFloat(msg.payload[n-10])
gs.sma = parseFloat(msg.payload[n-9])
gs.ecc = msg.payload[n-8]
gs.inc = parseFloat(msg.payload[n-7]).toFixed(4)
gs.raan = (parseFloat(msg.payload[n-6])).toFixed(4)
gs.aop = parseFloat(msg.payload[n-5]).toFixed(4)
gs.meananom = (parseFloat(msg.payload[n-4])+0.0).toFixed(4)
gs.meanmove = parseFloat(msg.payload[n-3]).toFixed(14)
gs.period = parseFloat(msg.payload[n-2])

// 090523 adding a null NAN undefiened detector it triggers also if all elements are null
msg.errorFlag=Object.values(gs).some((element) => isNaN(element)||element===null) || Object.values(gs).every((element) => element===0);
//
 
tab.push(gs)

msg.payload = tab
return msg;

<script>
  var audio = document.getElementById("audioPlayer");

  
  
  // Play the audio
  function playAudio() {
    audio.play();
  }

  // Pause the audio
  function pauseAudio() {
    audio.pause();
  }

  // Stop the audio and reset the playback time
  function stopAudio() {
    audio.pause();
    audio.currentTime = 0;
  }

  // Set the volume based on the provided value
  function setVolume(volume) {
    if (!isNaN(volume) && volume >= 0 && volume <= 100) {
      var normalizedVolume = volume / 100;
      audio.volume = normalizedVolume;
    }
  }
  scope.$watch('msg.payload', function(volume) {setVolume(volume);});
  // Initialize the volume on load
  

  // Play the audio on load
  document.addEventListener("DOMContentLoaded", function(event) {
    audio.play();
  });
  playAudio();
</script>
